transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the On Print Shop Designer Studio tutorial series.
In this video we will see what alignment rules are and how they work in the PDF block templates.
In PDF block templates, when you have created dependency rules, it affects the alignment of the blocks in the design.
To manage this, we create alignment rules.
These rules can be created for vertical blocks or horizontal blocks.
In the example here we have a business cards PDF block template.
So on the front end when the customer does not enter any value for the added blocks, the text blocks are displayed and to prevent this we create the dependency rule.
So, as per the dependency rule, whenever the customer provides any value for a block such as a phone number, then there will be space in the place of the phone number block.
To avoid this spacing issue and automatically adjust the alignment of the below blocks, alignment rules are created.
To create a rule, let's move to the admin panel.
Navigate to the Templates section and click on the PDF block templates.
Select the template, click on the actions drop down and select Manage Blocks.
On the Manage Blocks screen, locate the phone number text block.
So as per the block order we need to manage the fax block alignment.

So click on the manage properties link against the fax from the pop up, click on the add button from the properties drop down, select alignment rules in the reference block, select phone block as the alignment will be based on the phone block.
Then select the reference direction as vertical and click on save and back.
And you have successfully created an alignment rule for a PDF block.
Similarly, you can create the rule for cell and e-mail addresses on the front store.
When the customer chooses to skip entering the phone number value, the fax, cell and e-mail address blocks will move upward.
And there you have it.
Creating alignment rules for PDF block templates in on Print Shop is a breeze.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
